An aspirant for the All Progressives Congress (APC) national chairman, Senator Mohammed Sani Musa, has said despite the seemingly diverse interests, the ruling party was united and intact. He reiterated that President Muhammadu Buhari, as the leader of the party, was on top of the situation.   Obiano takes final bow, Soludo steps in Thursday     ‘We’re not aware Akpanudoedehe has resumed’     Why 12 per cent of NIMASA revenue can’t go to Maritime…   Speaking on Television Continental (TVC) News Tonight, Musa said if elected, he would strengthen the party structure in line with the ideology of its founding father and make a worthy institution as the largest in Africa. “Under my leadership, the party will embrace more technology in our operations which will reduce waste and abuse of our party best practices. “We’ll run a party that will preserve the legacy of our founding fathers to build a strong country that is more tolerant, more prosperous and fairer by giving every member of the party equal opportunity,” he said.